e `poi-ooxml-schemas` dependencies, and confirm that it relies on `xmlbeans 3.1.0`.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating testing approach**\\\\n\\\\nI’m noticing that the existing test has an exact handle called \\\\\\\"encryptione8b3doctype,\\\\\\\" which seems to be known already. To avoid having a brittle setup, I think it’s better to consider avoiding the use of this handle. I might need to look at a dynamic-access report that sees the active class, but there's no test file for that. Since our test does exist, I wonder if the coverage generator maps by class. I also think I should inspect the git diff.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_AvltC67JDAFJKrlkvmKWSyWJ|fc_0d831fc0ee1ec892016a11a4720ab881a1a5cb80cf0a78d860\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"git diff -- tests/src/org.apache.poi/poi-ooxml-schemas/4.1.2/src/test/java/org_apache_poi/poi_ooxml_schemas/SchemaorgApacheXmlbeansSystemSD023D6490046BA0250A839A9AD24C443TypeSystemHolderTest.java\", \"timeout\": 10}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 2124, \"output\": 889, \"cacheRead\": 12288, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 15301, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1779541093835, \"responseId\": \"resp_0d831fc0ee1ec892016a11a4663a0081a1b324d781daf592f7\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.poi:poi-ooxml-schemas:4.1.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-23T12-58-43-135083Z.log:520:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering compilation and dynamic access**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the need to compile and run tests, but it seems I should focus on inspecting the style instead. I have to avoid using dollar signs in names and think about line lengths and class names. \\n\\nI re